'''Stefan Rozental''' (born [[1903]] in [[Lodz]], [[Poland]], died [[1994]] in [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]]), was a [[Nuclear science|nuclear physicist]], specialising in [[quantum mechanics]]. He received his [[PhD|PhD]] from the [[University of Krak<U+00F3>w]] in [[1928]].

He later held an assistant position with [[Werner Heisenberg]] in [[Leipzig]] between [[1929]] and [[1934]], lectured in [[Krak<U+00F3>w]], between [[1934] and [[1938]] and was then, after [[Hendrik Anthony Kramers]] (which held the position from 1916) and [[L<U+00E9>on Rosenfeld]] (in that position from 1934) [[Niels Bohr]]'s personal assistant in [[Copenhagen]]. [[Denmark]]. 

=== Literature ===

* Stefan Rozental, ''Schicksalsjahre mit Niels Bohr'', DVA, 1991.
* Stefan Rozental, ''Niels Bohr: His Life and Work As Seen by His Friends and Colleagues'', John Wiley & Sons, 1964.

